race.comment: STERNIN (9) returned with a solid third at Werribee over 1000m after being in contention on the corner. Will present fitter and positions forward. Has the talent to take care of this field. WINGSANDPROPELLERS (5) has his third start and is close to a win. Improved again placing at Wodonga, and the on-pacer will get every chance from the inside gate. The likely danger. LARKIN (1) strode forward at Kyneton off a wide gate and folded right up. Three back he resumed in good order and we haven't seen the best of him. Has a 2kg claim today and is sure to be ridden more quietly. Can't be ruled out. MONIX (3) resumes and has jumped out well. He'd be a hope if presented on song. MAGNUS MAXIMUS (2) debuts and placed in a recent Wangaratta jumpout. Has a sticky barrier but is a betting watch.
